When did the House elect the Senate? Unless by that you meant the state legislatures electing state senators... but that's not the same thing...


 The members of the House of Representatives (1/2 of Congress) of each state would chose who would be their state's Senators. Since that is another example of indirect (yet) Democratic aspects of our system of government, we are a Republic.

